description.p:
In vivo animal experiments show that L-butylphthalide has the following functions:
1. significantly reducing the neural symptoms caused by cerebral injury-induced cerebral ischemia in rats;
2. reducing memory disorder induced by cerebral ischemia in rats;
3. reducing cerebral edema induced by cerebral ischemia in rats;
4. reducing cerebral apoplexy induced by cerebral ischemia in rats;
5. reducing the metabolic disorder of energy induced by cerebral ischemia in rats;
6. increasing cerebral blood flow in the ischemic region;
7. reducing behavioral disorder induced by ischemia in rats;
8. reducing the cerebral infarct area induced by cerebral ischemia in rats.
